library(DESeq2)
library(ggplot2)
counts <- read.csv("/Users/batulal-zubeidy/Desktop/TRGNFinal/TNB_HR_Joined_Counts.csv", header = TRUE, row.names = 1, sep = ",")
head(counts)
counts <- counts[which(rowSums(counts) >1),]
condition <- factor(c("TNB_Sample1", "TNB_Sample2", "TNB_Sample3", "TNB_Sample4", "TNB_Sample5", "TNB_Sample6", "TNB_Sample7", "TNB_Sample8", "TNB_Sample9", "TNB_Sample10", "HR_Sample1", "HR_Sample2", "HR_Sample3", "HR_Sample4", "HR_Sample5", "HR_Sample6", "HR_Sample7", "HR_Sample8", "HR_Sample9", "HR_Sample10"))
coldata <- data.frame(row.names = colnames(counts), condition)
